# 🎬 WatchInk Beta

> Sync Disney+ playback with friends in real time. Watch together, perfectly.

White & red modern Chrome extension + Node.js WebSocket server.

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
watchink/
├── extension/               ← Chrome Extension (load this in Chrome)
│   ├── manifest.json
│   ├── background.js        ← Service worker, manages WebSocket
│   ├── content.js           ← Injected into Disney+, sync engine + UI
│   ├── popup.html / popup.js ← Browser action popup
│   ├── styles.css           ← White/red overlay UI styles
│   └── icons/               ← Extension icons
│
└── backend/                 ← Node.js WebSocket server (deploy on Replit)
    ├── server.js
    ├── package.json
    └── .replit
```

---

## 🚀 Setup Guide

### Step 1 — Deploy the Backend on Replit

1. Go to **[replit.com](https://replit.com)** and create a new Repl
2. Choose **Node.js** template
3. Upload or paste the contents of `backend/server.js` and `backend/package.json`
4. Click **Run** — Replit will install deps and start the server
5. Copy your **Replit URL** (looks like `https://watchink-server.yourusername.repl.co`)
   - The WebSocket URL will be: `wss://watchink-server.yourusername.repl.co`

> **Note:** Replit free tier may sleep after inactivity. Use [UptimeRobot](https://uptimerobot.com) to ping `/health` every 5 minutes to keep it awake.

---

### Step 2 — Configure the Extension

Open `extension/content.js` and find line ~13:

```js
const CONFIG = {
  SERVER_URL: 'wss://watchink-server.onrender.com',  // production WebSocket endpoint
```

Replace with your Replit WebSocket URL:
```js
SERVER_URL: 'wss://watchink-server.yourusername.repl.co',
```

Also update `manifest.json` host_permissions to include your Replit domain:
```json
"host_permissions": [
  "https://www.disneyplus.com/*",
  "https://watchink-server.yourusername.repl.co/*",
  "wss://watchink-server.yourusername.repl.co/*"
]
```

---

### Step 3 — Load the Extension in Chrome

1. Open Chrome and go to: `chrome://extensions/`
2. Enable **Developer Mode** (toggle, top-right)
3. Click **"Load unpacked"**
4. Select the `watchink/extension/` folder
5. The WatchInk icon (🔴 play button) will appear in your toolbar

---

### Step 4 — Start a Watch Party

**Host:**
1. Open Disney+ and navigate to any content
2. The WatchInk modal will appear automatically
3. Click **"Create Room"**
4. Share the 6-character room code with friends

**Guests:**
1. Open Disney+ (same content — Disney+ doesn't enforce this, but sync works best when on the same episode)
2. Click **"Join Room"**
3. Enter the room code
4. Press play on the content — WatchInk will handle sync from there

---

## 🔁 How Sync Works

| Feature | Behavior |
|---------|----------|
| **Play/Pause/Seek** | Host actions are immediately broadcast to all guests |
| **Drift Correction** | Every 3s, guests compare their time vs host. If drift >500ms, playback rate adjusts softly; if >3s, hard seek |
| **Guest Override** | Guests can pause/seek but drift correction snaps them back within ~3s (keeps Disney+ controls intact) |
| **Next Episode** | Host URL change is broadcast; all guests navigate automatically |
| **Host Transfer** | If host disconnects, the next user becomes host automatically |
| **Reconnect** | Extension auto-reconnects up to 10 times on disconnect |
| **Mute Sync** | Users can toggle "Mute sync" to watch freely without being synced |

