## 🔧 Local Development

Run the backend locally:
```bash
cd backend
npm install
npm start
# Server runs on ws://localhost:3001
```

Keep `SERVER_URL: 'ws://localhost:3001'` in `content.js` for local testing.

---

## 🔐 Security & Compliance

- ✅ **No DRM bypass** — Only controls playback via the video element's standard API
- ✅ **No content capture** — Zero video data passes through our server
- ✅ **No auth interference** — Disney+ login/session untouched
- ✅ **No data storage** — Server holds room state in memory only, cleared on restart
- ✅ **Input validation** — All WebSocket events are validated server-side
- ✅ **URL safety** — Next-episode sync only allows `disneyplus.com` URLs
- ✅ **UUID room IDs** — 6-char alphanumeric codes with no personally identifiable info

---

## 🎨 UI Features

- **Welcome modal** — Create/Join room on first visit
- **Floating HUD** — Minimal widget while watching, shows room code + sync status
- **Sync indicator** — Green (synced) / Orange (drifting) / Red (desynced)
- **Latency display** — Real-time ping in milliseconds
- **Resync button** — Manual force-resync
- **Mute sync toggle** — Watch freely without being controlled
- **Copy room code** — One-click clipboard copy
- **User list** — See everyone in the room with host badge
- **Reconnecting banner** — Shown when socket drops

---

## ⚠️ Known Limitations

- Disney+ must be open in a tab (not a PWA window) for the extension to inject
- Free Replit instances may have ~500ms cold-start latency
- If Disney+ updates their video player DOM, `querySelector('video')` may need updating
- Sync works best on same network speeds; high-latency connections may drift more

